         <abstract id="aspace_16d6b4dd1fe4e4938580b7fea75dfadf">Correspondence, manuscripts, and other papers largely relating to Lyman Hotchkiss Bagg's interest in boating; his editorship of the <title render="italic">
               <part>Yale Literary Magazine</part>
            </title>, 1868-1869; and his weekly "College Chronicle" written for the <title render="italic">
               <part>New York World</part>
            </title>, 1876-1882. Also included are student translations from Latin and Greek, and correspondence and memorabilia from his years at Yale College, 1865-1869.</abstract>
